    <h1>what is information technology and computer science ?</h1>
    <h4>Information Technology (IT) is a broader field that encompasses the use and management of technology to handle and exchange information. It involves the design, development, implementation, and maintenance of computer systems, software, networks, and databases.

        Computer Science is more specific and focuses on the theoretical foundations of computation and the practical application of computer systems. It includes areas such as algorithms, programming languages, artificial intelligence, and the study of computing processes.</h4>
    <h4>In ITI (Industrial Training Institute), information technology (IT) typically refers to the use and management of computers, software, networks, and other technology-related systems in various industries. Computer science, on the other hand, focuses on the theoretical and practical aspects of computing, including algorithms, programming languages, and system design. ITI programs often cover a range of skills related to IT and computer science, preparing individuals for roles in technical support, networking, programming, and other related fields.</h4>
    
